180^\circ
\angle A + \angle B + \angle C = \angle A + 2 \angle C = 180^\circ 
\implies 40^\circ + 2 \angle C = 180^\circ \implies 2\angle C = 180^\circ - 40^\circ = 140^\circ
C
\angle B = \angle C = \dfrac{140^\circ}{2} = 70^\circ
\angle C + \angle ACD = 180^\circ\implies \angle ACD = 180^\circ - \angle C = 180^\circ - 70^\circ = 110^\circ
\angle ACD = 110^\circ
180^{\circ}
\angle BAC = 40^{\circ}
\angle ABC + \angle ACB = 140^{\circ}
AB=AC
\angle ABC = \angle ACB
\angle ABC = \angle ACB = 70^{\circ}
